Plot.
Plot.
Prepare yourself for an unparalleled sensory experience. Samsara reunites 
director Ron Fricke and producer Mark Magidson, whose award-winning films 
Baraka and Chronos were acclaimed for combining visual and musical artistry. 
Samsara is a Sanskrit word that means the ever turning wheel of life and 
is the point of departure for the filmmakers as they search for the elusive 
current of interconnection that runs through our lives. Filmed over a 
period of almost five years and in twenty-five countries, Samsara 
transports us to sacred grounds, disaster zones, industrial sites, and 
natural wonders. By dispensing with dialogue and descriptive text, 
Samsara subverts our expectations of a traditional documentary, instead 
encouraging our own inner interpretations inspired by images and music 
that infuses the ancient with the modern.
